      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thou shalt not wrest the judgment of thy poor — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As a judge should beware, lest through motives of compassion, or an affectation of popularity, he be biassed in favour of the poor; so, on the other hand, he must not despise a man because he is poor and without friends: he must not take advantage of his poverty to misrepresent his cause, to refuse to give him an impartial hearing, to strain a point of equity to his prejudice, or pass sentence wrongfully against him. The words ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "thy poor, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "are emphatical, importing that they were members of their body, though poor.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
